Disregard negative root. So possible x=1 or x=(3 + sqrt(13))/2. But x = a/b. If x=1, then a = b, and since a = c, then c = b, and since b = d, then d = b. So all variables equal. But as before, this leads to (2a)(2a) = a² + a² → 4a² = 2a² → 2a² =0, impossible. So x=1 is invalid. Thus, the only valid solution is x=(3 + sqrt(13))/2. So S = 2(r + 1/r). Let's compute this.
